entryComment: The consistency is harder than most other Mochies, the nutty and sweet aftertaste of this with the slight walnut taste makes this incredible.
The taste was very Surprising, something i havent really tasted before. The consistency is a bit mushy which fits perfectly to the strawberry like flavor.

Dried apple infused with white chocolate? Sounds interesting and certainly is! It tastes mostly like white chocolate and has only a hint of apple flavor to it, as someone who doesnt really like white chocolate thats a bit sad.
Im actually not too sure what it is specifically, i didnt really taste too much of it, it maybe has a slight rice syrup taste but thats pretty much it, has also no real texture. very underwhelming.
Better than the green one but it tastes very peppery. The texture is very similar but it doesnt feel like im biting on something empty.
Not a cookie, very hard and crunchy. No sweetness present and tastes EXTREMELY like black sesame. The taste is wayy too overpowering for my taste but for someone who loves black sesame thats a treat.

Smells like childhood, if you have ever smelled rice crackers then you recognize this smell and taste instantly. Adding honey to it and it tastes exactly like eating rice crackers with agave syrup but as a drink. Maybe a bit too much for one person alone.

That kind of surprised me at first, as it looks exactly like french macarons but the outer part of it is like empty eating paper and inbetween is a jelly filling. It is increadibly sweet so i couldnt eat much of it but it tastes really good nontheless.
Has zero taste, zero texture and vanished without me noticing. I am just confused.
This tastes Incredible. The dough reminds me a bit of sourdough and its very moist, with the perfectly sweet sweetpotato pieces in there its just the perfect cake. I wish it would be a bigger piece!

It has a nice, mushy texture but after biting into it it feels more like eating powder. Generally a bland taste but somehow theres a weird aftertaste to it which i didnt like. Great potential but failed in the end.

The outer shell reminds me of this thick eating paper, inside of it is a sweet paste which isn't a pur√©e like consistency but still has some small pieces in there, i love it but there is something missing to it which i cannot quite tell.
Wasn't even able to open (or eat) it.
Tasted like a good Baumkuchen with a bit of powdered sugar. Moist inside and slight vanillary aftertaste. A bit too dense to eat it as is but with something to drink it together its perfect.

Increadible smell but thats the only increadible thing about it. The texture is like those dried bacon chips but theres no real flavor to it. Its like a rice cracker with squid arome, you only really taste something when eating alot of it which is more or less the whole thing.
I was expecting peanuts or something but thats defenitely not it. Its like a nut but hollow inside of it with a weird black sesam spiciness which i dont like.
Traditional japanese luck games, exactly my kind of thing. Good sweet taste and funny sharing with others and discussing what would happen in the future.

This one was kind of weird, the outside is very moist and mushy but you can clearly feel the harder inside, its like when slightly squeezing an eggplant. The bean paste in it has a really nice texture and taste and the parts where you get paste and dough is really good.
